`assets\license.rtf` is outdated as it refers to 'PowerShell 6'.

Since #8846, we do not show an EULA in the MSI, so we should remove `license.rtf`.

@TravisEz13 appears to be in favour of removing RTF generation: https://github.com/PowerShell/PowerShell/issues/8704#issuecomment-461667561
